The receiver is 1944. The rifle is in amazing condition and runs flawlessly, I put 40 rds through it to check functionality. I was planning on keeping it but will consider trades for an AR10 or AR in 308 only. I have over $1500 in this rifle and will only consider trades of equal value, I may consider a PTR-308 if it has extras. Just a little history on the T26 , during WWll the army cut down M1 garand rifles and assembled a small number of T26's for testing to use in jungle warfare, they never made it into production and all but two were turned back into rifles while the other two (1 Springfield) (1 Winchester) were put into museums, there are no other surviving T26 garands in existence. All T26 Garands in civilian hands are post war commercial guns, most T26's like this one do have WWll era receivers.
